<br>
IC:<br>
<br>
Dear Friends<br>
<br>
You are cordially invited to participate in the Bazaar of the Bizarre.  For the convenience of all citizens of Norrath, with the aid of a little magical tinkering, a new option has been arranged to allow adventurers and travelers to sell, barter, and exchange their goods.  Because after all, commerce is the heart of any thriving community.  No need to hang on uselessly to what we don’t need, when it might be exchanged for something we do need.<br>
<br>
In a little used corner of the Bazaar on Luclin, there is an odd magical device.  Please don’t try to interfere with it, as it is both quite delicate and also well shielded.  This device is your key to communication with all other like-minded traders seeking to buy or sell their goods.  Simply place your hand on the flat surface on top of the device to attune yourself to it.  Or send a factor to do so in your place.  And don’t be too disturbed by the whispering you’ll hear in the back of your mind.  You’ll get used to it, and instances of permanent mental instability have been relatively few.<br>
<br>
There are no rules to the dealing that may take place using this resource.  Use your best discretion and mind your reputation as well as your pocketbook.  Civility is expected, but nothing else, and all are welcome.<br>
<br>
Special thanks to Coriolis for the advanced enchanting theory that went into the crafting of this device, and to Sabbik for the tinkered elements.  Not that I pretend to understand exactly how they work.<br>
<br>
Sincerely,<br>
Valquiss Silverpalm<br>
Saga<br>
<br>
OOC:<br>
<br>
It’s come to my attention that quite a few players are discontented with the ooc chatter on the current Market channel.  Buying and selling is a part of playing EQ, but it really doesn’t have to intrude on the atmosphere of the game the way the current Market channel seems to, and it can be in character.  It can be very rewarding in character, actually, as many have discovered via auction.  And now it’s time to bring that to the new channel system available to us.<br>
<br>
There is a new channel available called “RPMarket.”  It is just what the name implies, an in-character market channel for the purposes of buying and selling.  Use it or don’t use it as you wish, but please respect the intent of the channel.  It probably won’t be as popular as the current Market channel, and there is nothing to stop anyone from being on both, but I’ve already heard from a few people they intend to use this channel exclusively so there should be plenty of opportunities for commerce here, once things get rolling along.<br>
<br>
Now, there is no way to really moderate this channel, or any other channel.  The moderation commands default to whoever has been on a channel longest, so really no one will ever be in change.  What I am relying on to keep this channel to it’s stated purpose is a strong community of people who want this to work.  There is a decent core of people already on this channel (saw 20 yesterday) and hopefully this community can be self-policing, to whatever extent that it needs to be policed, which will hopefully be small.  If someone is going out of character on this channel (and be sure it’s out of character, because snarkiness might be in-character, but discussing the Oscars clearly isn’t) please remind them politely but firmly of the purpose of this channel.  And in my opinion such reminders are best issued via private tell.  Correcting someone over the open channel is both out of character of itself and also tends to provoke defensiveness.  But use your best judgement.  This channel belongs to all of us, and will be completely beyond my control or anyone’s once it is in use.<br>
<br>
Again, the channel is “RPMarket.”  And please consider /autojoin for this channel, because even if you may not be looking to buy or sell at any given time, having people on the channel and keeping it to it’s intended purpose will lend it credibility.  Hopefully this channel will be fun and unintrusive to be on even when you don’t need it.  That’s certainly the goal.<br>
<br>
Thanks in advance.<br>
<br>
Player of Valquiss<br>
